<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871209-0127 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Consolidated Natural Gas Co.</HL><DD> 12/09/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CNG </IN><TEXT>   Consolidated Natural Gas Co. set its 1988 capital budget at $426 million, up 15% from an estimated $369 million this year.    The Pittsburgh-based natural gas production and distribution company said the new budget will fund substantial increases in its drilling program, reflecting expectations of improved conditions in exploration and production.    Under the 1988 budget, exploration and production spending will rise to $238 million from about $210 million this year. Consolidated said it expects to drill 500 wells next year, up from 370 in 1987. </TEXT></DOC>